

1. Quarry / Geological Source — connects monuments to the landscapes they came from, enabling studies of historical quarrying and trade.
2. Architectural Function of Each Stone — distinguishes where different materials were used (foundations, walls, columns, carvings, roofing, paving), revealing material selection strategies.
3. Stone’s Contribution to Outstanding Universal Value (OUV) — explicitly captures whether and how the building material contributes to the site’s heritage significance, creating a bridge between geology and UNESCO heritage evaluation.10. Stone Characteristics

